 felt the rain plunking on top of his metal dome as he trudgedthrough the muddy puddles of the bog he was headed for the sanctuary of hut and soon his optical sensors picked up the golden glow shining through itswindows as he neared the inviting house he felt a relief that at last hewould get out of this annoying persistent rain 
 but when he tried to pass through the entrance he discovered that his inflexibledroid body just could not get in he tried from one angle then from another at lastthe perception that he was simply the wrong shape to get in seeped into his computermind 
