 the princess looked in a scared way at her eyesglittering close to her the red patches on her face came and it was plain that she understood nothing and was so frightenedthat her fear would prevent her understanding any of her explanations however clear they might be whether it wasthe fault or the this same thing happened everyday the princess eyes grew dim she could not see and could not hearanything but was only conscious of her stern withered faceclose to her of his breath and the smell of him and could think onlyof how to get away quickly to her own room to make out the problemin peace the old man was beside himself moved the chair on whichhe was sitting noisily backward and forward made efforts to controlhimself and not become vehement but almost always did becomevehement scolded and sometimes flung the exercise book away 
 the princess gave a wrong answer 
