 princess mary went back to her room with the sad scaredexpression that rarely left her and which made her plain sicklyface yet plainer she sat down at her writing table on which stoodminiature portraits and which was littered with books and princess was as untidy as her father was tidy she put down thegeometry book and eagerly broke the seal of her letter it was fromher most intimate friend from childhood that same julie karaginawho had been at the rostovs party 
